# Study Materials

Study material resources contain user inputted study aids for the associated subject.

A study material is created when the User has added study aid information.

## Study Material `data` Structure

> Below is the structure of an `study_material` `data` object

```
{
  "id": <integer>,
  "object": <string>,
  "url": <string>,
  "data_updated_at": <date>,
  "data": {
    "created_at": <date>,
    "subject_id": <integer>,
    "subject_type": <string>,
    "meaning_note": <string_or_null>,
    "reading_note": <string_or_null>,
    "meaning_synonyms": <array_of_strings>
  }
}
```

Attribute | Possible Values | Description
--------- | --------------- | -----------
`created_at` | Date | Timestamp when the resource was created.
`subject_id` | Integer | Unique identification related to one `subject` resource. See [Subjects](#subjects).
`subject_type` | `Kanji`, `Radical`, or `Vocabulary` | The subject type the `study_material` is related to. See [Subjects](#subjects).
`meaning_note` | String | Subject meaning related note the user inputted
`reading_note` | String | Subject reading related note the user inputted
`meaning_synonyms` | String | Meaning answer synonyms the user inputted. These are used as correct answers, along with WaniKani defaults for reviews.

